December 1952 and FOLIO ==
December 1952 is perhaps Brown's most famous score.
December 1952 consists purely of horizontal and vertical lines varying in width, spread out over the page; it is a landmark piece in the history of graphic notation of music.
According to dates on the scores, Brown wrote December 1952 and then moved back towards forms of notation that contain more specific musical information.
